证据片段: The author has reported the failure of a cold-worked Zr-2.5Nb tube at 1.8 percent hoop strain. This specimen failed between 0 and 3440 h so that the creep rate must have been 5 × 10^-6 per h or greater.

证据片段: Coleman² has shown that at a creep rate of 5 × 10^-6 per h for cold-worked Zr-2.5Nb, in-reactor, the stress exponent of creep rate, n, is about 10

证据片段: Stress-rupture tests on cold drawn Zr-2.5Nb, quenched and aged Zr-2.5Nb, and cold drawn Zircaloy-2 (out-ofpile uniaxial) showed that rupture ductility can be correlated with n the lower n, the higher the ductility³
